From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Crelia <crelia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] NeoForge FlowerPotBlock Potted Getter

Annotates the existing getPotted() method in FlowerPotBlock as the NeoForge
coremod target for the ReplaceFieldWithGetterAccess transformation. The method
already exists in this Folia version, so this patch only adds a marker comment.

NeoForge's coremod replaces direct GETFIELD access to the potted field with
calls to this getter method, allowing mods to intercept or redirect what block
a FlowerPotBlock is considered to contain.

diff --git a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/block/FlowerPotBlock.java b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/block/FlowerPotBlock.java
index 7194565ad1a910fe300d8664a30b35c4eff18cb7..662bd46e460cbbf335dfd56274fd9936e0c90e5e 100644
--- a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/block/FlowerPotBlock.java
+++ b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/block/FlowerPotBlock.java
@@ -127,6 +127,7 @@ public class FlowerPotBlock extends Block {
             : super.updateShape(state, direction, neighborState, world, pos, neighborPos);
     }
 
+    // NeoForge: getPotted() below is used by coremod ReplaceFieldWithGetterAccess for potted field
     public Block getPotted() {
         return this.potted;
     }
